<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4688bb85-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s6064"><num value="6064">§ 6064.</num><heading> Signature presumed authentic</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The fact that an individual’s name is signed to a return, statement, or other document shall be prima facie evidence for all purposes that the return, statement, or other document was actually signed by him.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id4688bb86-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/749">68A Stat. 749</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
